The paper deals with the problem of subspace tracking, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper also discusses the problem of missing data and matrix completion, which are also common problems in these fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI), which are all relevant to the problem at hand.
